Hi all,
I do appreciate your kind suggestions, and will definitely take Doxygen into account. The reason why I'm not using it at the moment is that I could be freer to organize the structure of a manually edited document, and that's why I titled this project as "Rcpp Notes". It's a kind of draft at the current stage, and hopefully it could be synchronized to Doxygen when the content is rich enough.
Another more technical reason that I feel hard to control Doxygen is that Rcpp uses some macros and includes to define constructors and functions, which cannot be recognized by Doxygen directly. I'll try to figure it out in the future.
